    <!-- 
        The <head> section contains metadata about the webpage.
        This includes the page title, character encoding, links to fonts, and stylesheets.
    -->

    <title>My Recipe</title>
    <!-- 
        The <title> tag defines the text shown in the browser tab.
        Here, it’s set to “My Recipe.”
    -->

    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <!-- 
        The <meta> tag defines the character encoding (UTF-8),
        which allows proper display of special characters and symbols.
    -->

    <!-- 
        These <link> tags load fonts from Google Fonts.
        “preconnect” helps browsers connect faster by setting up early connections.
    -->
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>

    <!-- 
        This link imports a custom font called “Vend Sans” from Google Fonts.
        The font can then be used in the CSS file.
    -->
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Vend+Sans:ital,wght@0,300..700;1,300..700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

    <!-- 
        This link connects the HTML file to an external CSS stylesheet named “styles.css.”
        The CSS file controls how the page looks (colors, layout, fonts, etc.).
    -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="styles.css" />
</head>

<body>
    <!-- 
        The <body> section contains all the visible content of the web page:
        text, images, and other elements the user interacts with.
    -->

    <div class="top">
        <!-- 
            This <div> contains the main title and introduction to the recipe.
        -->
        <h1>How To Make Ukrainian Borscht</h1>
        <p>
            Borscht is a sour soup originating from Eastern Europe, most famously known as a bright red beetroot soup.
            It is served hot and made with vegetables like cabbage, carrots, and potatoes, often using a meat or vegetable stock.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="left">
        <!-- 
            This section (with class “left”) likely appears on the left side of the page.
            It contains the image, prep time, total time, servings, and ingredients.
        -->
        <div>
            <!-- Displays an image of the soup -->
            <img src="https://veselka.com/cdn/shop/articles/Studio_Session-050_20x20_b9c2da51-c1c3-4713-926b-04282641ef19.jpg?v=1701885404"
                width="600" />
        </div>

        <div id="prep_time">
            <!-- Shows how long preparation takes -->
            <b>PREP TIME:</b>
            <p>15 mins</p>
        </div>

        <div id="total_time">
            <!-- Shows total cooking time -->
            <b>TOTAL TIME:</b>
            <b>3 hours 45 minutes</b>
        </div>

        <div id="Serving">
            <!-- Displays number of servings -->
            <h4>SERVINGS:</h4>
            <p>8-10</p>
        </div>

        <div>
            <!-- 
                Lists the ingredients for both the broth and the soup.
            -->
            <h2>INGREDIENTS</h2>
            <h4>Borscht Broth</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>1.5 pounds beef short ribs</li>
                <li>¼ large onion, cut into quarters</li>
                <li>1 carrot, cut into big chunks</li>
                <li>2 bay leaves</li>
                <li>6-7 black peppercorns</li>
                <li>1 Tbsp salt</li>
                <li>12 cups water</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Borscht</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>2 Tbsp oil, divided</li>
                <li>1 medium onion, diced small</li>
                <li>2 cloves garlic chopped + 3-4 cloves garlic sliced</li>
                <li>2 carrots, peeled and grated</li>
                <li>2 large beets, peeled and grated</li>
                <li>1 tsp sugar</li>
                <li>4 Tbsp tomato paste</li>
                <li>3 medium Yukon potatoes, peeled and cut into small chunks</li>
                <li>5 cups shredded cabbage</li>
                <li>2 Tbsp fresh dill, chopped</li>
                <li>sour cream, to serve</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="right">
        <!-- 
            This “right” section likely appears to the right of the image and ingredients.
            It contains step-by-step cooking instructions and extra content.
        -->
        <div>
            <h3>INSTRUCTIONS</h3>
            <!-- Ordered list for recipe steps -->
            <ol>
                <li>Combine short ribs, onion, carrot, celery, bay leaves, peppercorns, salt, and water in a pot.</li>
                <li>Boil, then simmer for 2.5 to 3 hours until meat falls off bones. Skim off scum as needed.</li>
                <li>While simmering, sauté onion, garlic, and carrots until soft. Set aside.</li>
                <li>Sauté beets separately with sugar, vinegar, and tomato paste. Cook until tender.</li>
                <li>Remove ribs, shred meat, and return to broth with potatoes. Simmer 15 minutes.</li>
                <li>Add onion/carrot mixture and cabbage. Cook 10 minutes.</li>
                <li>Add beets and simmer another 8 minutes.</li>
                <li>Stir in dill and sliced garlic; simmer 2 minutes more.</li>
                <li>Let sit 30 minutes before serving with dill and sour cream.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div>
            <!-- Provides a link to another Borscht recipe -->
            <h2>Additional Borscht Recipes...</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://veronikaskitchen.com/borscht-soup-recipe/#recipe">Borscht Soup Recipe</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>

